HEADWORD: Monotonous
<hw>Mo*not"o*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>mo`nos</grk> alone, single + <?/ tone. See <er>Tone</er>.]</ety>
<def>Uttered in one unvarying tone; continued with dull uniformity;
characterized by monotony; without change or variety; wearisome.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Mo*not"o*nous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mo*not"o*nous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

